#: ../../D/Datamation.rst:9
msgid ""
"A magazine that many hackers assume all :ref:`suit`\\s read. Used to "
"question an unbelieved quote, as in \"Did you read that in "
"*Datamation?*\\\". It used to publish something hackishly funny every once "
"in a while, like the original paper on :ref:`COME-FROM` in 1973, and Ed "
"Post's *Real Programmers Don't Use Pascal* ten years later, but for a long "
"time after that it was much more exclusively :ref:`suit`\\-oriented and "
"boring. Following a change of editorship in 1994, Datamation briefly tried "
"for more the technical content and irreverent humor that marked its early "
"days, but this did not last."
msgstr ""
"多くのハッカーが\\ :ref:`suit`\\ なら誰もが読んでいると思い込んでいる雑誌。「Did you read that in "
"*Datamation?*」(それDatamationで読んだのか?)のように、信じがたい引用を疑問視するのに使う。かつては時折、1973年の\\ "
":ref:`COME-FROM`\\ に関する原論文や、その10年後のEd Postの『*Real Programmers Don't Use "
"Pascal*』のような、ハッカー的に面白いものを掲載していたが、その後は長い間、もっぱら\\ :ref:`suit`\\ "
"向けで退屈なものだった。1994年の編集長交代後、Datamationは初期の特徴だったより技術的な内容と無遠慮なユーモアを一時的に目指したが、これは長続きしなかった。"
